🎤 HOW TO PRESENT IN CLASS

Follow this structure:

1️⃣ Introduction (2 mins)

Define firewall + real-life example.

2️⃣ Why It Is Important (2 mins)

Talk about CIA Triad.

3️⃣ Types of Firewall (5 mins)

Explain 4 types clearly.

4️⃣ How It Works (3 mins)

Traffic → Rules → Allow/Block.

5️⃣ Limitations (Very Important!)

Mention what it cannot do.

6️⃣ Conclusion

> Firewall is the first line of defense in network security.



Lecturer will love that sentence.


---

❓ Questions They May Ask You

Q1: Can firewall stop virus?

Answer: It can block suspicious traffic, but antivirus is needed to remove malware inside system.


---

Q2: Can firewall stop DoS?

Answer: It can reduce small attacks but large DDoS needs advanced protection.


---

Q3: What is difference between router and firewall?

Answer: Router connects networks. Firewall filters traffic based on security rules.

(Some routers have built-in firewall.)


---

Q4: What happens if firewall is misconfigured?

Answer: It can either block legitimate traffic or allow attackers inside.


